  <h7><p>Questions 9-12</p></h7>
  <p>Which FOUR pieces of advice about writing a CV does the speaker give?</p>
  	<ol id="targetspotting">
  <list class="answerList">
  <li><a id="t1">You should find out about the company you are applying to.</a></li>
  <li><a id="t2">You should make your CV stand out from other applicants' CVs.</a></li>
  <li>  <a id="t3">You should be careful not to make any mistakes.</a></li>
  <li>  <a id="t4">You should use white paper for your CV.</a></li>
  <li>  <a id="t5">You should be truthful on your CV.</a></li>
  <li>  <a id="t6">You should limit the length of your CV.</a></li>
  <li>  <a id="t7">You should keep a copy of your CV for yourself.</a></li>
  </list>
</ol>

</section>

<section id="fb1">
  <p class="feedbacktext">A. Mary does not mention this at all.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb2">
  <p class="feedbacktext">B. Mary says your CV should be unique and 'attract an employer's attention'. In other words 'stand out'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb3">
  <p class="feedbacktext">C. Mary says that accuracy is important and that you shouldn't make any spelling, grammar, punctuation or spacing errors. The word 'errors' has the same meaning as 'mistakes'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb4">
  <p class="feedbacktext">D. Mary does not mention the paper you should use.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb5">
  <p class="feedbacktext">E. Mary says that honesty is important and that you should never include false information on your CV. 'Honesty' means the same as 'truthfulness'.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb6">
  <p class="feedbacktext">F. Mary says that conciseness is important too. She says that your CV should never go beyond two sides of A4 paper. In other words, limit the length.</p>
</section>

<section id="fb7">
  <p class="feedbacktext">G. Mary doesn't mention this.</p>
</section>

